WeightVolumeConversions

cube: 1"
dice: 1/2" - 1/4"
mince: 1/8"

1 cup = 8 oz = 16 tbsp = 240 ml
1 tbsp = 0.5 oz = 3 tsp = 15 ml

1 lbs = 16 oz = 454 g
1 oz = 28.35 g

corn starch has twice the thickening power of flour

buttermilk: combine 1 cup milk to 1 tbsp vinegar and let test 10 minutes
baking: replace buttermilk with milk and baking soda with 2x baking powder


dried herb volume = fresh herb volume / 3
garlic powder: 1/2 tsp = 1 fresh clove

tomato sauce = 2 part water to 1 part tomato paste

one serving pasta = 85g -> 320 Calories 
2 ml meat sauce per g of raw pasta
less for smooth sauce 

one serving potato = 6 oz per person -> 156 Calories
salted water = 1 tsp per quart

tube pan: 9" to 10"
square pan: 8"x8"x2" = 20cm x 20cm = 2 1/4 quarts
round pan: 9"x2-3"
rectangular pan: 13"x9"x2" = 4 quarts
loaf pan: 9"x5" = 2 1/3 quarts

sanitizing
clean with warm soapy water
rinse with warm water
apply solution of 15 ml bleach to 4 l of water for at least 1 minute
air dry

halibut = flétan
haddock = aiglefin
cod = morue
flank steak = bavette
skirt steak = hampe
hanger steak = onglet

beef or lamb
rare 130
medium-rare 135
medium 145
medium-well 150
well-done 160


pork
medium-well 145


large roast cooked @ 450 will increase 15 while resting
medium roast cooked @ 250 will increase 10 while resting
grilled meat will increase 20-25 while resting

min internal temperature recommended by USDA
|cooked fruits or vegetable that will be held for a length of time before eaten|135|
|beef pieces |145|
|seafood|145|
|fish|145|
|eggs for immediate service|145|
|ground meat|155|
|eggs|155|
|pork|160|
|poultry|165|
|everything else|165|

beef where the inside has not been in contact with anything,
ground, tenderized or injected in any kind,
can be safely cooked to lower temperature

baking done temperature
traditional and pound cake 205-210
quick bread and muffins 200-205
custard and crème brulée 170-175
rich dough breads 180–190
lean dough breads 190–210
molten and lava cake 160
bread pudding and quiche and meringue pies 160
cheesecake 150
brownie 195 ( 165-205 )

Cake done when
The edges of the cake pull away from the sides of the pan.
It smells fragrant.
The top and edges are golden brown (or look matte for chocolate cake).
A toothpick or paring knife comes out clean.
The cake springs back when pressed gently.





